and skin","Between the pelvic peritoneum and pelvic fascia"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edeep perineal pouch\u003C/strong\u003E is located between the pelvic diaphragm superiorly and the perineal membrane (previously called urogenital diaphragm) inferiorly. It contains the external urethral sphincter, deep transverse perineal muscle, and associated neurovascular structures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial perineal pouch\u003C/strong\u003E lies between the perineal membrane and the superficial perineal fascia. It contains the bulb of the vestibule, greater vestibular glands, and the erectile tissues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe space \u003Cstrong\u003Ebetween the pelvic diaphragm and pelvic peritoneum\u003C/strong\u003E is not a perineal pouch - it is part of the retroperitoneal space. The area \u003Cstrong\u003Ebetween the perineal fascia and skin\u003C/strong\u003E contains superficial fat and connective tissue. The space \u003Cstrong\u003Ebetween the pelvic peritoneum and pelvic fascia\u003C/strong\u003E is part of the extraperitoneal space.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The deep perineal pouch lies between the pelvic diaphragm superiorly and the perineal membrane inferiorly","The superficial perineal pouch lies between the perineal membrane superiorly and the perineal fascia inferiorly","The perineal pouches contain important neurovascular and muscular structures"],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Bolla SR, Hoare BS, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Deep Perineal Space. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538272/","Kovacs, W. J., \u0026 Ojeda, S. R. (Eds.). (2012). Textbook of endocrine physiology. OUP USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47661"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15677"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47661"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-17T12:59:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-17T13:02:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8368"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62215"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4931"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb4","name":"Musculoskeletal","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T09:50:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"13"}},"heading":{"data":null